WEBVTT

00:02.300 --> 00:02.567
- Previously,

00:02.567 --> 00:03.033
- Previously,
on "Below Deck"...

00:05.433 --> 00:07.400
- Chris, Chris?
This is the captain.

00:07.433 --> 00:09.300
I'm just wondering
why I don't hear Chris.

00:09.300 --> 00:11.300
- Hey, Chris?
- Yeah, I'm up. Ugh, f---.

00:11.300 --> 00:13.233
- You know, you're gonna be
dumb, you've got to be tough.

00:13.266 --> 00:14.700
He's a whole lot of one
and not much of the other.

00:14.734 --> 00:16.433
- Hi.
- How are you?

00:16.433 --> 00:19.000
- This is really why
I got into yachting.

00:19.033 --> 00:20.433
You meet a hot sailor who's
got a beautiful sailboat.

00:20.433 --> 00:22.100
Hey, this is nice.

00:24.433 --> 00:26.300
- Yeah.

00:26.333 --> 00:28.233
- I think Nico's adorable,
but he has a girlfriend,

00:28.266 --> 00:30.000
and I'm not gonna get
in the way of that.

00:30.033 --> 00:31.000
- I miss you.

00:33.300 --> 00:36.033
- Listen, you're breaking up.
- I want the one on the star.

00:36.033 --> 00:37.433
[laughter]

00:37.433 --> 00:39.333
- Are you guys getting
along right now?

00:39.367 --> 00:41.333
- She sucks at her job,
but she's hilarious.

00:41.333 --> 00:43.467
- It's insulting, and it's
definitely out of line.

00:43.467 --> 00:45.567
- You're so wonderful.
- Thank you.

00:45.600 --> 00:47.266
- Bri and I have
chemistry together.

00:52.333 --> 00:53.633
- Bri's pretty.
She's a pretty girl.

01:06.200 --> 01:08.033
- Jen likes to drink.

01:13.066 --> 01:15.133
- Nobody comes
between me and Jesus.

01:19.333 --> 01:20.600
[horn blares]

01:20.633 --> 01:23.600
[upbeat music]

01:23.633 --> 01:30.600
♪ ♪

01:35.533 --> 01:37.567
[upbeat club music]

01:37.600 --> 01:40.166
- [indistinct]

01:40.200 --> 01:44.233
♪ ♪

01:44.233 --> 01:46.300
- Here we go. Here we go.
Here we go. Here we go.

01:46.333 --> 01:51.433
♪ ♪

01:56.066 --> 01:58.066
- Jen?
- What?

01:58.100 --> 02:01.066
- What are you doing?
- I'm good. I just am drunk.

02:01.100 --> 02:03.200
I don't want to be like this.
I never get this way.

02:03.233 --> 02:05.133
Ever! Ever.

02:05.133 --> 02:07.266
- I know, me either.
- I want to go to bed.

02:07.266 --> 02:09.333
- I like Jen.
I can't explain it.

02:09.367 --> 02:13.000
But she's having a full-fledged
dramatic telenovela meltdown.

02:13.033 --> 02:14.400
I'm leaving without you.
I'm getting a cab.

02:14.400 --> 02:16.500
Bye.

02:19.266 --> 02:20.367
[sighs]

02:23.300 --> 02:26.600
all: Baker! Baker! Baker! Baker!

02:31.100 --> 02:33.266
The way I see it, I can either
go back to the boat

02:33.266 --> 02:36.500
and hang out with
drunk crewmembers,

02:36.533 --> 02:38.533
or I can go with hot Jesus

02:38.567 --> 02:40.633
on his private sailboat
and hang out with him.

02:40.667 --> 02:42.233
- Let's go home,
and get sleep, then.

02:42.266 --> 02:43.667
- You're funny.

02:43.700 --> 02:45.133
- What would Jesus do?

02:45.166 --> 02:46.433
Come on.

02:46.433 --> 02:47.533
Me.

02:48.567 --> 02:50.433
- Hey, I have
a question for you.

02:50.433 --> 02:52.433
I know you love your seat back,
but like, I'm--

02:52.467 --> 02:54.433
- F---off. Sit right there.
Don't look at me like that.

02:54.433 --> 02:56.300
You can both sit up here.
I can lay on the seat.

02:56.300 --> 02:58.300
- I'm not moving.
No, I'm not moving.

02:58.333 --> 02:59.400
- You can sit right here.
I have a whole seat for you.

02:59.433 --> 03:00.467
I'm not. I'm done.

03:01.433 --> 03:04.233
[soft upbeat music]

03:04.266 --> 03:06.233
- There you go.
- Oh.

03:06.266 --> 03:07.467
- I need--I need help. Thanks.

03:16.433 --> 03:17.667
- F---my life.

03:17.700 --> 03:19.433
- Where did Kate disappear to?

03:19.467 --> 03:21.567
- [indistinct]
- [laughs] That sucks.

03:21.600 --> 03:25.200
♪ ♪

03:25.200 --> 03:26.567
- [burps]

03:30.567 --> 03:33.200
- Can you help me
with my hangover?

03:33.233 --> 03:34.300
- Mm-hmm.

03:34.333 --> 03:36.567
- [soft laugh]

03:44.633 --> 03:47.467
- Okay, look here.
- All right.

03:47.467 --> 03:51.600
- I feel like honest and
intention--intentional today.

03:51.600 --> 03:56.066
- Okay.
- I enjoy your friendship.

03:56.100 --> 03:57.467
It's like, really nice to, like,

03:57.467 --> 03:59.333
be able to really connect
with somebody else.

03:59.367 --> 04:01.200
- Yep.

04:01.200 --> 04:02.333
- Vulnerability
looks good on me.

04:02.333 --> 04:03.467
Pretty girls like that sh--.

04:03.467 --> 04:05.400
You're a hard read, by the way.

04:05.433 --> 04:08.367
- I'm hard to read?
What would you like to clarify?

04:08.367 --> 04:12.200
- Where are you at?
What's up with you?

04:12.233 --> 04:16.233
- I totally appreciate you
being honest with me.

04:16.233 --> 04:17.300
Interesting me...

04:18.500 --> 04:23.200
But I am not currently
romantically attracted to you.

04:27.633 --> 04:30.100
- We should sleep soon.

04:30.133 --> 04:33.166
That feels better to get that
little conversation over with.

04:36.233 --> 04:39.200
[upbeat music]

04:39.233 --> 04:43.500
♪ ♪

04:43.500 --> 04:46.467
[alarm blaring]

04:46.500 --> 04:47.734
- [groans]

04:54.533 --> 04:56.500
- Guys, I was crunk last night.

04:56.533 --> 04:59.266
all: Baker! Baker! Baker!

04:59.300 --> 05:00.667
- How are you feeling?
- I feel fine.

05:00.667 --> 05:02.500
- You're very happy.

05:02.533 --> 05:05.133
I, on the other hand,
was not very happy.

05:05.133 --> 05:06.400
- How was your night?
You weren't happy?

05:06.433 --> 05:09.500
- I wanted my bed.

05:09.533 --> 05:11.533
- Anybody seen Kate
this morning?

05:11.533 --> 05:12.734
- No idea.

05:12.767 --> 05:16.266
- I think she's... at church.

05:16.266 --> 05:18.233
Getting baptized.

05:18.667 --> 05:21.667
[idle music]

05:21.700 --> 05:25.133
♪ ♪

05:25.166 --> 05:27.400
- [laughs]

05:27.400 --> 05:28.734
Oh, it's you, okay.

05:31.300 --> 05:32.767
The best thing about
waking up early

05:33.000 --> 05:34.700
is catching the walk of shame.

05:34.700 --> 05:36.633
- You are naughty.

05:36.667 --> 05:38.166
- This is gold to me.

05:38.200 --> 05:39.533
- Um, hi!

05:39.567 --> 05:42.300
- Yeah.
- [slow clapping]

05:45.400 --> 05:48.367
- Somebody was naughty-yachty!

05:48.400 --> 05:51.533
Maybe, maybe she'll be
a happier Kate.

05:51.567 --> 05:54.767
- I guess that answers my
question as to where Kate's at.

05:56.433 --> 05:58.667
- Deck guys, let's help
Bruno on the dock.

05:58.700 --> 06:01.533
Let's go, seriously.
Don't drag it on the dock.

06:01.567 --> 06:04.166
Do not drag that on the dock.
Let's move, Chris.

06:04.200 --> 06:05.700
Come on, princess.

06:05.734 --> 06:09.166
So, what we'll do is
chamois, fold it here,

06:09.200 --> 06:10.633
and then put it in the last.
- Yep.

06:10.667 --> 06:13.734
- Can you throw down
a chamois mop?

06:13.734 --> 06:15.734
- It's upstairs.
You guys get it.

06:15.734 --> 06:18.200
- The thing about Chris
is he just doesn't care.

06:18.200 --> 06:21.200
On a scale to one
to not giving a sh--,

06:21.200 --> 06:24.300
he's sh-- his pants.

06:24.333 --> 06:26.400
- Oh. I'd like to sleep.

06:26.433 --> 06:28.734
- Hey, Jen, did you
toast me a bagel?

06:28.767 --> 06:30.400
- I did.

06:30.433 --> 06:32.333
It was waiting for you
in the toaster.

06:32.333 --> 06:34.467
- Thank you. I about
broke my ankle last night.

06:34.500 --> 06:36.233
It's a miracle I didn't.

06:37.467 --> 06:39.400
- Mm-hmm.

06:39.433 --> 06:42.734
- Church? Was Jesus there?
- Yes, Jesus was there.

06:42.734 --> 06:44.433
Jesus came.

06:44.467 --> 06:46.300
I saw God twice.

06:46.333 --> 06:50.300
- That must have been some mass.
- Mm-hmm.

06:50.333 --> 06:54.066
- So it needs to be, like,
nice and soft.

06:54.100 --> 06:56.033
- Whatever pays the bills.

07:04.533 --> 07:06.233
[hip-hop instrumental music]

07:06.233 --> 07:07.633
- Look at that.
- Oh!

07:07.667 --> 07:09.700
Is that from last night?

07:09.734 --> 07:10.734
- Those are.

07:12.600 --> 07:16.233
He like, pow!
- [laughs]

07:16.233 --> 07:17.767
- [laughs]
You need some sun.

07:17.767 --> 07:21.600
We should take the ironing board
outside onto the deck.

07:21.633 --> 07:23.367
- Yeah, okay.
You can do that.

07:23.367 --> 07:24.767
- Really?
- Yes.

07:24.767 --> 07:27.233
- And wear our bikinis
while we iron?

07:27.233 --> 07:28.633
- Yeah, you want to do it?
- Hell, yeah, buddy.

07:28.667 --> 07:30.500
- Go change.
- All right, yes.

07:30.500 --> 07:35.266
I can't wait to be
outside in the sun!

07:35.266 --> 07:37.667
- Deckhands' lucky day.
- I know, I know.

07:37.700 --> 07:39.500
- Listen, I signed up for
six weeks of charter,

07:39.533 --> 07:41.400
not six weeks of rehab.

07:41.400 --> 07:43.000
On our turnover day,
I'm gonna have a beer,

07:43.000 --> 07:45.400
'cause it's the only time
we can.

07:45.400 --> 07:48.100
- Holy sh--.
- Hey, Nico, you want to chat?

07:48.133 --> 07:49.633
- Yeah, I just want to check
my emails really quick.

07:49.667 --> 07:51.000
Is that okay?

07:51.000 --> 07:52.533
- Yeah.
- F---ing...

07:52.533 --> 07:53.600
- Have you been able to talk
to your girlfriend

07:53.633 --> 07:55.400
since you've been here?

07:55.400 --> 07:57.400
- Well, it's been hard,
because I've been--

07:57.400 --> 08:01.400
- Mm-hmm.
- Sorry, you're distracting me.

08:01.400 --> 08:03.266
Yeah, you know what?

08:03.266 --> 08:06.533
Sometimes you need
to just get some alone time.

08:06.533 --> 08:09.767
- What the hell is going on?

08:10.000 --> 08:11.500
[line trilling]

08:14.667 --> 08:16.734
Sorry.
[sniffling]

08:17.000 --> 08:18.533
No, I'm like,
you know, when, like,

08:18.567 --> 08:20.433
someone's, like,
overly compensating,

08:20.433 --> 08:23.533
like acting like
everything's fine.

08:23.567 --> 08:26.100
It's just not, you know?
[sniffling]

08:26.133 --> 08:30.033
Just, it's just a lot, you know?

08:30.033 --> 08:33.300
I just want to be
home right now.

08:33.300 --> 08:36.033
I'm so worried about Mom.

08:36.066 --> 08:38.700
I can't fix anything
when I'm here, you know?

08:38.700 --> 08:40.667
And I've always
been there for her.

08:40.700 --> 08:44.433
And if she's not okay,
it's gonna f---me up, you know?

08:44.433 --> 08:46.433
Like, I can't deal with that.

08:46.433 --> 08:48.033
From the beginning
of the season,

08:48.033 --> 08:50.300
I just wanted to be home
with my family.

08:50.333 --> 08:52.433
It's hard dealing with
losing your best friend

08:52.467 --> 08:54.433
and your little brother.

08:54.433 --> 08:56.433
It's hard on my mom,
it's hard on my family,

08:56.467 --> 08:58.300
and it's not really fair
for me to not be there

08:58.333 --> 09:00.433
to support my brothers
and my family.

09:05.500 --> 09:06.734
- Coming up...

09:06.734 --> 09:08.533
- What the f--- are they doing?

09:11.367 --> 09:13.066
[loud clank]

09:13.066 --> 09:15.000
- Did I hit something?
- God damn it!

09:19.200 --> 09:19.433
[upbeat music]

09:22.467 --> 09:24.133
- Kate, Matt, Nico,

09:24.166 --> 09:27.066
I need you guys
in the crew mess ASAP.

09:27.066 --> 09:29.000
♪ ♪

09:29.033 --> 09:31.467
Sports fans.
- Hi.

09:31.500 --> 09:34.467
- We have
Susan Winters Macintosh.

09:34.500 --> 09:37.600
She's a luxury real estate agent
in the Palm Springs area,

09:37.600 --> 09:40.033
which is a pretty
high-rent area.

09:40.066 --> 09:44.367
We have eight, which is two more
than we've had in the past,

09:44.367 --> 09:46.467
and they're all women.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.767
Girls getting together to get
sh--faced and have some fun.

09:49.000 --> 09:50.600
If this crew steps
up to the plate,

09:50.633 --> 09:52.467
this should be
a walk in the park.

09:52.500 --> 09:54.467
They want to do
a disco-themed dance party.

09:54.500 --> 09:56.467
- Yeah.
I mean, disco theme party?

09:56.500 --> 09:58.200
Come on, it's played out.

09:58.233 --> 10:00.467
But at least it's not
an '80s theme party.

10:00.500 --> 10:03.600
- Chef, I don't see anything
in there that's really crazy.

10:03.633 --> 10:05.066
- Okay.

10:05.100 --> 10:06.734
- So, we are gonna
get bombarded.

10:06.767 --> 10:09.367
We'll just take it as it comes
and make it work.

10:09.367 --> 10:11.700
There's a lot of work left
to be done on the boat.

10:11.734 --> 10:14.633
So let's pack it in, guys.
- Yay.

10:14.633 --> 10:16.633
[radio beeps]
- All deck crew.

10:16.667 --> 10:20.767
Can you go to the bow?
Let's just talk about docking.

10:20.767 --> 10:23.400
I want to go through
tying down the boat again.

10:23.433 --> 10:26.400
I need to train them
to use the lines.

10:26.433 --> 10:27.734
The more bodies
we have on deck that are

10:27.767 --> 10:30.000
actually capable
of doing things,

10:30.000 --> 10:32.500
the more smooth this
whole thing is gonna run.

10:32.533 --> 10:34.600
You're gonna go
over once, right?

10:34.633 --> 10:36.633
- Oh, yeah. And then like that.
- There you go. Put it through.

10:36.667 --> 10:39.500
- The drunk sailor climbs out
the hole, goes around the pole,

10:39.533 --> 10:41.667
and falls back in the hole.
- Sure, if that works.

10:41.700 --> 10:44.533
And if someone else
wants to grab this one.

10:44.533 --> 10:47.200
- Last I heard, I wasn't
allowed to touch the lines.

10:47.233 --> 10:49.133
And I like it that way.

10:49.166 --> 10:50.500
But I guess
I should probably do the job

10:50.533 --> 10:52.533
I've been hired to do now.

10:52.533 --> 10:55.133
- That, and tying a bollard,
and then making off lines

10:55.133 --> 10:56.600
are the three things
you should know as a deckhand.

10:56.633 --> 10:57.767
- Is that one right?
- Easy.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.200
- I learned it on YouTube.

10:59.233 --> 11:00.500
- No, no. Okay, hold on.

11:00.533 --> 11:02.000
Oh, no.

11:02.033 --> 11:05.433
- Oh, okay. So...

11:05.467 --> 11:07.166
- Uh, no. Not at all.
- Wait, like this?

11:07.166 --> 11:08.767
- So why don't we not
confuse yourself?

11:09.000 --> 11:10.667
- No, the other way--
- All right.

11:10.700 --> 11:12.533
Whatever side you start on,
you go opposite of.

11:12.567 --> 11:14.700
- So it's basically like this?
- Uh-huh.

11:14.700 --> 11:16.567
- And then--
- Underneath.

11:16.567 --> 11:17.767
- Like this?
- In it.

11:18.000 --> 11:20.033
Easy, right? Yeah.

11:20.066 --> 11:22.433
I need to put this in action,
and they need to get going.

11:22.433 --> 11:23.700
- Perfect.
- All right.

11:23.734 --> 11:26.700
[pensive music]

11:26.734 --> 11:29.667
♪ ♪

11:29.700 --> 11:31.700
[sighs] Oh, man, I'm so
f---ing stressed out.

11:31.700 --> 11:34.300
- Huh?
- Just a lot going on.

11:34.300 --> 11:35.667
- Do you want to talk about it?

11:37.700 --> 11:39.066
Do you want to sit outside?

11:42.300 --> 11:45.033
- If you're on this boat,
you know, working hard,

11:45.066 --> 11:46.734
and you're holding in
all this stress and stuff,

11:46.734 --> 11:48.200
it's gonna become a problem.

11:48.200 --> 11:50.600
So I am naturally a nurturer,

11:50.600 --> 11:52.266
and I'm happy to be that person
for Nico right now,

11:52.300 --> 11:54.734
because I can tell he needs it.

11:54.734 --> 11:55.767
- How are you doing?

12:25.600 --> 12:28.100
- Oh. I'm a beginner.

12:28.133 --> 12:30.033
Let me just make that clear.

12:30.066 --> 12:34.300
[plays ukulele]

12:34.333 --> 12:37.233
- You know, it's super hard
being away from Melissa.

12:37.233 --> 12:40.066
And I think that's why me
and Bri maybe get along so well,

12:40.100 --> 12:43.233
is because she reminds
me of my girlfriend.

12:47.000 --> 12:49.633
She's awesome, and
I see her as a good friend.

12:49.667 --> 12:51.066
♪ ♪

12:51.100 --> 12:53.100
Can I play?
- Do it.

12:53.100 --> 12:55.734
[upbeat music]

12:55.767 --> 12:58.367
♪ ♪

12:58.367 --> 12:59.767
- Just trying to wake up.

13:00.000 --> 13:01.667
[blender whirs]

13:04.767 --> 13:07.633
- So, we have three hours
'till the guests arrive.

13:07.633 --> 13:09.767
We have to work extra,
extra fast.

13:10.000 --> 13:12.000
- We're going to put out
some water toys today.

13:12.033 --> 13:15.533
- I want you to go around and do
a quick, quick, quick vacuum.

13:15.533 --> 13:17.266
- Let's start with a wipe-down
this morning.

13:17.266 --> 13:18.667
- You want us to re-do
the windows, too?

13:18.700 --> 13:21.100
- Yes.
- Wiping windows.

13:21.133 --> 13:22.133
- Go, go, go.

13:22.133 --> 13:25.133
[lively music]

13:25.133 --> 13:26.767
♪ ♪

13:27.000 --> 13:28.667
- One hour 'till guests arrive.

13:28.667 --> 13:31.633
So, anything we need to step up,
let's get it done.

13:31.667 --> 13:34.633
- Fast, fast, fast, fast.
Ooh.

13:34.667 --> 13:37.233
- I feel like
I have my groove down.

13:37.266 --> 13:40.200
[vacuum humming]

13:40.233 --> 13:42.000
But I don't want
to get too comfortable,

13:42.033 --> 13:43.767
because as soon as you
get comfortable,

13:44.000 --> 13:45.667
that's when
the curve ball is thrown.

13:45.667 --> 13:47.667
[sighs]

13:47.667 --> 13:49.000
- Will you disperse the flowers
while I just

13:49.000 --> 13:51.033
make sure we have everything?

13:51.033 --> 13:53.767
- Rinse it off with fresh water,
and then make sure it's dry.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.300
- Cool.
- You already got ice?

13:55.333 --> 13:57.133
And you already
stocked the water?

13:57.166 --> 14:00.033
- Champagne is on ice.
I will go grab ice downstairs.

14:00.033 --> 14:01.400
- Bruno, grab some cleaner wax.

14:01.433 --> 14:03.567
You can do this whole top here.
- Cool.

14:03.567 --> 14:05.700
- Lee, Lee. I've been helping
the deckies out with the lines.

14:05.700 --> 14:08.367
Are you comfortable with them
helping us get off the dock?

14:08.400 --> 14:10.266
- All right. Let's do it.

14:10.300 --> 14:12.166
- Deck guys, let's go ahead

14:12.166 --> 14:14.133
and start getting
changed over.

14:14.734 --> 14:18.166
[upbeat electronic music]

14:18.166 --> 14:20.700
- Kathleen, she looks like Vicki
from the Housewives to me.

14:20.700 --> 14:23.000
- Really? I feel like
they all kind of do.

14:23.033 --> 14:25.633
- I need everyone
on the main deck aft.

14:25.667 --> 14:29.033
- Copy.

14:29.033 --> 14:31.700
- How exciting.
[scattered whoos]

14:31.734 --> 14:34.200
- God, I hate that sound.
- I know.

14:34.200 --> 14:35.333
- Hello!
- Hello!

14:35.333 --> 14:37.066
- Hi.
- Hi.

14:37.066 --> 14:38.200
- Welcome aboard.
I'm Captain Lee.

14:38.200 --> 14:40.066
- Hi.
- Hello.

14:40.100 --> 14:42.000
- Hi, Captain Lee,
I'm Susan. Nice to meet you.

14:42.033 --> 14:43.667
- It's a pleasure.
- Hi, welcome. I'm Kate.

14:43.700 --> 14:45.266
- Kate, nice to meet you.
- Hi, I'm Jen.

14:45.300 --> 14:47.266
[women cheering]

14:47.300 --> 14:50.333
- Are you guys ready for us?
[laughter]

14:50.333 --> 14:52.266
- I know this charter already.

14:52.300 --> 14:54.133
A lot of whoo-ing and yeah-ing.

14:54.166 --> 14:57.033
- Yeah!
[cheering]

14:57.066 --> 14:59.700
- A lot of straw hats.

14:59.734 --> 15:02.066
- Kate will show you around
the boat and give you a tour.

15:02.066 --> 15:04.066
And we'll get out of here
and we'll get the party started.

15:04.066 --> 15:05.600
If that's all right with you.
[cheering]

15:05.633 --> 15:07.333
All right. Good. Kate?

15:07.367 --> 15:10.000
- Right this way, ladies.
- Okay, great.

15:10.033 --> 15:12.734
- Watch your--
- Oh my gosh.

15:12.767 --> 15:15.100
- This is our main salon.
- Oh, look at the flowers.

15:15.100 --> 15:17.033
Do we get to take them with us?
[laughs]

15:17.066 --> 15:19.233
- I'm not gonna check your bags.

15:19.233 --> 15:21.066
So, right this way.

15:21.100 --> 15:23.367
And this is
your master stateroom.

15:23.367 --> 15:25.200
[women gasping]
And then right this way.

15:25.233 --> 15:27.166
- Cheers, honey girl,
you made it happen.

15:27.200 --> 15:29.300
[electronic music]

15:29.333 --> 15:31.367
- That was a heavy one, guys,
don't break your back.

15:31.367 --> 15:33.367
- There might be a body
in that one, huh?

15:33.367 --> 15:35.734
- That goes in the master.
- There's a live body in there.

15:35.767 --> 15:37.367
- We have the Jacuzzi,

15:37.367 --> 15:39.367
and then up here
we have the bunny patch.

15:39.367 --> 15:41.367
- This is beautiful.

15:41.367 --> 15:43.066
- Hey, Susan,
you're making me nervous.

15:43.100 --> 15:45.066
I need you to come back.

15:45.100 --> 15:47.767
- Okay, and now, I'm gonna show
y'all your guest quarters, yeah?

15:47.767 --> 15:49.333
- Your room is stunning,
but this is still killer.

15:49.367 --> 15:51.100
- It is.
- It's killer.

15:51.100 --> 15:52.233
- We're leaving the dock
right now?

15:52.266 --> 15:53.300
- Then we want to go see it.

15:55.367 --> 15:56.400
- Let's do it.

15:56.400 --> 15:59.000
[rousing music]

15:59.033 --> 16:00.767
- Pull, pull, pull, pull, pull.

16:01.000 --> 16:02.500
- Bow line's off.
He's coming to the stern.

16:02.533 --> 16:04.266
- Loosen up, loosen up,
loosen up, loosen up, loosen up.

16:04.266 --> 16:06.066
- What's he doing?

16:06.100 --> 16:07.767
- Pull, pull,
pull, pull, pull, pull.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.066
That's good.
- I need the spring line done.

16:10.100 --> 16:12.000
- What do you guys want to do?
- Let's go up. Let's go up.

16:12.033 --> 16:13.266
- It's really happening,
you guys.

16:15.033 --> 16:16.667
- Come on, pull it.

16:16.667 --> 16:18.266
- Let's go.
Let's get that stern line off.

16:18.266 --> 16:19.400
- Let go, let go.

16:19.433 --> 16:22.734
- What the f--- are they doing?

16:22.767 --> 16:24.467
That's ridiculous.

16:24.500 --> 16:26.700
Cap, our bow's sticking here.

16:29.266 --> 16:30.233
- I'm waiting on the dock guy.

16:31.767 --> 16:34.200
- Bow's just kicking closer
and closer and closer.

16:34.233 --> 16:35.233
F---.

16:35.266 --> 16:36.233
- Watch the bow!

16:38.533 --> 16:40.367
[loud clank]
God damn it!

16:40.400 --> 16:41.700
[dramatic music]

16:41.734 --> 16:43.033
- Oh, God.

16:43.033 --> 16:46.133
- Did we hit something?

16:46.166 --> 16:47.433
- I kept hollering at them,

16:47.433 --> 16:49.166
get that f---ing
spring line off.

16:49.166 --> 16:51.300
I've got a knot in my stomach,

16:51.300 --> 16:53.133
because that could easy do

16:53.166 --> 16:55.233
a 1/4 of a million dollars
worth of damage.

16:55.266 --> 16:57.166
- Oh my gosh.
- That's what happens

16:57.200 --> 16:59.033
when people aren't f---ing
paying attention.

16:59.033 --> 17:00.433
- Did we hit?
- Yeah, we it.

17:00.433 --> 17:02.033
What the f---
happened back here?

17:07.233 --> 17:08.300
- We're waiting on the dock guy.

17:09.700 --> 17:11.233
[loud clank]
- God damn it!

17:11.266 --> 17:12.700
- Oh, the bow!

17:12.700 --> 17:15.166
- Oh, God.
Did it hit something?

17:19.700 --> 17:22.033
- All right,
let's tidy this up.

17:22.066 --> 17:24.333
- I am madder
than a pissed-on chicken.

17:24.333 --> 17:26.166
- Oh, f---ing bow to stern.

17:26.200 --> 17:29.000
Everyone needs to start f---ing
paying attention.

17:29.033 --> 17:30.333
Captain Lee's right there.
You got to go that way.

17:30.367 --> 17:32.200
I would stay clear
of him as well.

17:32.200 --> 17:34.166
- Yeah.
- Here we go, girls!

17:34.200 --> 17:36.400
[cheering]

17:36.433 --> 17:39.467
[upbeat music]

17:39.500 --> 17:42.467
♪ ♪

17:42.500 --> 17:45.033
- That, to that,
we can bring this.

17:45.066 --> 17:46.734
- You did nothing to
this coffee, right?

17:46.734 --> 17:48.734
- It's mine.
- Okay, 'cause the Captain Lee

17:48.734 --> 17:50.700
wants some, and-- he's had a
little bit of a stressful time.

17:50.734 --> 17:53.700
I'm gonna take your coffee.

17:53.734 --> 17:56.200
- How's the captain, though?
- We hit the dock, you know?

17:56.233 --> 17:58.033
- He's pretty mad.
- Yeah.

17:58.066 --> 17:59.266
- Do you think it was something
that we did wrong?

17:59.300 --> 18:01.333
- It's a mistake on our part,

18:01.367 --> 18:03.233
and we're definitely
gonna have to pay for it now.

18:03.233 --> 18:06.100
There's so much just
building up inside me.

18:06.100 --> 18:08.033
All these guys aren't where
they're supposed to be.

18:08.066 --> 18:11.033
But who's in charge of
these guys? The senior deckhand.

18:11.066 --> 18:12.333
- Nico to the bridge.

18:14.233 --> 18:17.367
How bad's the scratch?
- Not that bad.

18:17.367 --> 18:19.100
- Who did we have back there?

18:19.133 --> 18:20.233
Chris?
- It was Chris and Baker.

18:20.233 --> 18:22.166
- Two of my deck crew,

18:22.200 --> 18:23.500
they're standing there
looking at the dock guy,

18:23.500 --> 18:25.300
watching him screw up,

18:25.333 --> 18:27.367
and don't open their mouths.

18:27.367 --> 18:30.233
It's really obvious that they
don't know what they don't know.

18:30.233 --> 18:32.100
I'll get somebody
down to touch it up.

18:32.100 --> 18:33.233
- All right.

18:33.233 --> 18:34.333
- Dumbasses.

18:34.367 --> 18:38.066
[upbeat music]

18:38.100 --> 18:42.233
[women cheering]

18:43.433 --> 18:44.467
- Yes, of course.

18:45.400 --> 18:46.400
- I'll bring the bottle.

18:46.433 --> 18:48.200
How about that?

18:48.233 --> 18:52.233
- She--she learns quick!
[laughter]

18:52.266 --> 18:55.266
- Is the captain pretty pissed?

18:55.266 --> 18:57.000
- We'll just stay clear of him.

18:57.000 --> 18:58.266
- Yep.
Just do our jobs anyways.

18:58.266 --> 19:00.200
- Do our jobs.
Move on.

19:00.233 --> 19:01.400
- So is--the boat's damaged?
- Yeah.

19:01.400 --> 19:03.400
- It wasn't me, man.

19:09.433 --> 19:12.266
- Look at how calm the water is.
- I know.

19:12.266 --> 19:14.667
- You're our new BFF.
- Yes! [laughs]

19:14.700 --> 19:16.000
- We have snacks
coming right up.

19:16.000 --> 19:17.033
- Okay.

19:20.133 --> 19:22.367
- [laughing] I'm like, what?

19:22.400 --> 19:26.166
Sex? I mean, maybe--
maybe tomorrow.

19:26.200 --> 19:28.133
[laughter]

19:29.166 --> 19:31.166
- Totally f---ed up, right?
- Mm-hmm.

19:31.166 --> 19:32.300
- No, it was insane,
because I was literally

19:32.300 --> 19:35.400
seeing what was about to happen.

19:35.433 --> 19:37.433
You know, like, 'cause now it
makes sense for me.

19:37.433 --> 19:39.166
And I knew, like,
if you don't get the lines out,

19:39.166 --> 19:41.033
it's gonna pull the ship back.

19:41.033 --> 19:42.433
- Mm-hmm.
- And it's gonna hit so hard.

19:42.467 --> 19:43.567
- And that's exactly
what happened.

19:43.567 --> 19:45.367
I was f---ing pissed.

19:45.400 --> 19:48.033
- Is this meat on this?
What's on it?

19:48.033 --> 19:50.166
Don't they normally
send two dockhands?

19:50.200 --> 19:51.533
- Regardless of the dockhands,

19:51.567 --> 19:53.567
that was our fault.
- Yeah.

19:53.600 --> 19:56.433
- Doesn't matter. He walked
right past the spring line.

19:56.467 --> 19:59.500
And no one said anything.
And then he was on the stern.

19:59.533 --> 20:01.433
F---ing everything.

20:01.433 --> 20:04.433
[upbeat music]

20:04.433 --> 20:07.066
♪ ♪

20:07.066 --> 20:09.567
- Beautiful.
- Oh.

20:09.600 --> 20:11.433
- How's it going out there?
- Good.

20:11.467 --> 20:13.600
They're very happy.
How's it going with you?

20:13.600 --> 20:15.333
- Horrible.
- What happened?

20:15.367 --> 20:17.600
- We f---ing smashed the dock.
- Yeah.

20:17.600 --> 20:19.400
Well, I heard
the dock people screaming,

20:19.433 --> 20:20.533
and Captain was not happy.

20:20.567 --> 20:22.166
- We smashed the hull into it.

20:22.200 --> 20:23.667
Not really happy
with them right now.

20:23.700 --> 20:27.467
- Time to shine.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.667
- Hey, Baker.
Just so you know,

20:29.700 --> 20:32.166
like, that's not
single-handedly,

20:32.200 --> 20:35.200
like, his fault, your fault;
it's everybody fault.

20:35.233 --> 20:38.166
F---ing Chris is like, "Oh,
you know, it wasn't my fault."

20:38.200 --> 20:40.333
Like, that guy is just like,
on my f---ing

20:40.367 --> 20:42.133
last nerve right now, so.

20:42.166 --> 20:44.200
- We definitely f---ed up.
Again.

20:44.200 --> 20:46.066
You can't just say it's not
your fault.

20:46.066 --> 20:48.400
We're a team.

20:49.633 --> 20:52.166
Captain Lee, the anchor's
ready on your command.

20:52.200 --> 20:54.100
- On my mark. Drop.

20:54.100 --> 20:57.166
[metal chain whirring]

20:57.200 --> 20:58.200
- You see that color, right?

20:58.734 --> 21:00.133
- Yeah, you see it?

21:03.233 --> 21:05.500
- Captain, 2 1/2 in the water.

21:05.533 --> 21:07.300
- Oh, this is awesome.

21:07.333 --> 21:09.367
- Look at how pretty.

21:09.367 --> 21:11.100
- Okay, the guests are
all there. You can plate.

21:11.133 --> 21:12.633
- Excellent.
I'll start plating now.

21:12.633 --> 21:14.300
Every group
has their highs and lows.

21:14.333 --> 21:16.367
- Is the eggplant parmesan
really gonna

21:16.367 --> 21:18.433
go good with tequila?

21:18.467 --> 21:20.433
- I'm sure it'll be fine.
- Okay.

21:20.467 --> 21:23.166
- The kind of chef I am,
I love fresh fish.

21:23.200 --> 21:25.066
I love organic meats.

21:25.100 --> 21:26.633
You know, keep it fresh,
keep it simple.

21:26.667 --> 21:30.500
I can make anyone food
they want to eat and will enjoy.

21:30.533 --> 21:33.500
We have chicken Chinese salad
with some sesame seeds.

21:33.533 --> 21:36.400
- Perfect.
- Oh, that looks really good.

21:36.400 --> 21:38.266
- It smells so--
- Oh, I know.

21:38.300 --> 21:39.600
- Doesn't it?
- [laughs]

21:39.633 --> 21:41.500
- Yeah.
- Awesome.

21:41.533 --> 21:43.367
- This is excellent.
- Oh. Oh my gosh, it's amazing.

21:43.400 --> 21:44.734
- They're happy, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

21:44.767 --> 21:47.600
all: Cheers!

21:47.633 --> 21:50.667
- There we go.
- Then it sucks.

21:50.667 --> 21:53.533
- Oh my God.
- Is Jen back up?

21:53.533 --> 21:55.400
- No, not yet.
I'm gonna go--get her.

21:55.433 --> 21:57.467
- Maybe she's just doing
laundry or something.

21:57.500 --> 21:59.467
- You did so good today.
- That means a lot.

21:59.500 --> 22:01.533
Because, like, service
has always been like, ugh.

22:01.533 --> 22:03.266
- You're early, girl, so

22:03.300 --> 22:04.767
go do the crew platters now

22:05.000 --> 22:06.533
- Okay.
- And go on break at four.

22:06.533 --> 22:08.400
And you...

22:08.400 --> 22:11.300
are on guest service
and putting things away.

22:11.300 --> 22:13.233
- Got it. Yay.

22:13.266 --> 22:15.667
- I want you to check on
the guests every seven minutes.

22:15.700 --> 22:17.633
- Got it.

22:17.667 --> 22:20.166
- Put the stuff on the counter
in the cupboards where it goes.

22:20.166 --> 22:23.400
Stop touching that and touch
this, and clean that plate.

22:23.433 --> 22:25.367
- Thought you were gonna tell me
to put that away, put this down?

22:25.400 --> 22:27.166
- Okay, put those--
put that in the trash can.

22:27.166 --> 22:29.266
- Don't touch that, touch this.
I've got it, this.

22:29.300 --> 22:30.367
- I'm just trying to keep you
focused on the task at hand.

22:30.400 --> 22:31.567
- I have to read your mind.

22:31.567 --> 22:33.166
- Everything was just amazing.

22:33.166 --> 22:34.667
- They want
a disco party tonight.

22:34.700 --> 22:36.567
- Right.
- And I have looked everywhere.

22:36.567 --> 22:38.300
- You've got to go
shopping for balls.

22:38.333 --> 22:39.433
- Right.
We don't have them on board.

22:39.467 --> 22:41.433
- Okay.

22:41.433 --> 22:43.433
- Bri is on break until 6:00.
- Right.

22:43.467 --> 22:45.400
- So it is you keeping
the guests happy.

22:45.433 --> 22:47.433
Every seven minutes,
talk to the guests.

22:47.433 --> 22:49.433
- Micromanagement?
- You need it.

22:49.433 --> 22:51.500
- Kate micromanaging me
would be an understatement.

22:51.533 --> 22:53.467
And even though I'm
the newest one on the boat,

22:53.467 --> 22:55.700
I find it very difficult
to bite my tongue.

22:55.734 --> 22:58.700
[upbeat music]

22:58.734 --> 23:00.333
- [cheers]

23:00.333 --> 23:01.567
- Get it, Susan.
- [laughs]

23:01.600 --> 23:05.200
- Whoo!
- [laughs]

23:05.200 --> 23:07.700
- Captain, just letting you
know, I'm going to shore.

23:07.734 --> 23:09.700
Wish me luck.
I hope they have disco balls.

23:09.734 --> 23:12.533
[both screaming]

23:12.567 --> 23:14.600
Oh, God. This is so stupid.

23:14.600 --> 23:17.300
I mean, you're kind of taking up
a lot of room up here, buddy.

23:17.333 --> 23:19.433
Could you just move?
Could you just move?

23:19.467 --> 23:21.467
- Hold her! Hold her!
Hold her!

23:21.467 --> 23:25.200
- Hold me.
God damn it!

23:25.200 --> 23:26.734
- Hi. Champagne and water?

23:26.767 --> 23:30.400
- I would love a water,
and a Sauvignon blanc.

23:30.433 --> 23:33.166
- Okay, no problem.
- Thank you.

23:33.200 --> 23:34.567
- Hey, would you do me
a huge favor?

23:34.600 --> 23:36.333
Would you run up
to the sky lounge

23:36.367 --> 23:37.767
and get a bottle of
Sauvignon blanc?

23:37.767 --> 23:39.333
- I'm busy right now.
- Oh, are you?

23:39.367 --> 23:41.433
Okay, I'm sorry.
- Yeah.

23:41.467 --> 23:45.367
- [mumbling "A Whole New World"]
- [soft laugh]

23:45.400 --> 23:47.500
- My ex-girlfriend and I dated
for 1 1/2 years.

23:47.533 --> 23:50.767
Right before the season,
I decided to cut it off.

23:51.000 --> 23:54.367
- You can show me the world?
- I--I have--I can.

23:54.367 --> 23:55.767
And right now,
I'm looking to have some fun.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.233
- [laughs]
- [playful groaning]

23:58.266 --> 23:59.467
Perhaps with Bri.

23:59.500 --> 24:01.333
- [laughing]
- Okay.

24:01.367 --> 24:03.367
- Sauvignon blanc.

24:03.367 --> 24:06.633
Okay, so I have a
Sauvignon blanc and a champagne.

24:06.633 --> 24:08.367
- Oh, I'll take the champagne.
- Awesome.

24:08.367 --> 24:09.467
- You know what
I would love is a beer.

24:09.500 --> 24:11.233
- She's drinking it.

24:11.266 --> 24:12.300
- Yeah, everybody else
is still good?

24:15.266 --> 24:16.533
[laughter]
- I was gonna say--

24:16.533 --> 24:18.333
I'll be right back with that.

24:18.367 --> 24:20.367
I'll bring you
another champagne.

24:20.400 --> 24:22.667
Oh, come on. Why do these
things keep disappearing?

24:22.700 --> 24:27.000
- What are you looking for?
- The beer opener?

24:27.000 --> 24:28.400
Where is the wine key?

24:28.433 --> 24:30.400
- Jen is so lost.
[laughs]

24:30.433 --> 24:31.533
- Ugh.

24:31.533 --> 24:32.767
- "Ugh."
- Ugh!

24:33.000 --> 24:34.667
- Aggressive grunting.

24:34.700 --> 24:36.667
It's like a train wreck.
You have to keep looking.

24:36.700 --> 24:38.767
- I'm gonna set these over here.

24:39.533 --> 24:40.567
- Okay.

24:41.000 --> 24:43.233
- Yeah!
Ugh.

24:43.266 --> 24:45.400
I don't know why Kate gave
Brianna the afternoon off,

24:45.433 --> 24:48.533
because these guests
are a handful.

24:48.533 --> 24:50.767
Am I in a Twilight Zone?
Is this normal?

24:53.700 --> 24:55.767
- Okay.
- So maybe the refrigerator

24:56.000 --> 24:58.367
that they're kept in
isn't cold enough.

24:58.400 --> 25:00.033
- Yes, I will grab one
out of another fridge.

25:00.033 --> 25:02.300
[sighs]
It's just a free-for-all.

25:02.333 --> 25:04.033
- Come on, kiddo.

25:04.033 --> 25:06.033
- Bruno, it might be easier
to attach now.

25:06.033 --> 25:08.400
[hip-hop instrumental music]

25:08.433 --> 25:10.266
- Pull it, pull it.
There you go.

25:10.300 --> 25:12.266
- Careful with that line.
There you go.

25:12.300 --> 25:14.433
You can even use the yellow line
to pull yourself in.

25:14.467 --> 25:17.033
Okay, let's hurry up.
[motor humming]

25:17.033 --> 25:19.433
No, no, no. Manually do it
with your hand. Push it.

25:19.433 --> 25:23.400
There we go. Good job, Bruno.
Good job, Baker.

25:23.433 --> 25:24.567
♪ ♪

25:24.600 --> 25:25.633
- Hi, Chris.

25:27.033 --> 25:28.400
- Great.

25:28.433 --> 25:29.700
I'm just a real busy guy here,

25:29.700 --> 25:32.033
always working.

25:32.066 --> 25:34.400
- Chris, where are you?
Where is he?

25:34.433 --> 25:36.567
- On the platform,
putting away the swim stuff.

25:36.567 --> 25:38.633
- Come up here and help us
put away this slide.

25:38.667 --> 25:43.066
[motor whining]

25:43.066 --> 25:45.333
- Lift it more,
a little more, Nico.

25:45.333 --> 25:47.533
Let's pull it. Let's pull it.

25:47.567 --> 25:50.333
Look, Nico, the blue one on top.

25:50.367 --> 25:52.000
- Okay.
- What?

25:52.033 --> 25:53.333
- You want us to move that up
and put it on there?

25:53.367 --> 25:54.734
- Come on, man. Yes.

25:54.734 --> 25:56.333
- Yeah, do you understand
how much that weighs?

25:56.367 --> 25:57.600
Smoking that peace pipe, dog.

25:57.600 --> 25:59.033
- Let's go, Chris.

25:59.066 --> 26:00.600
After we hit the dock, I got

26:00.600 --> 26:02.333
Bruno and Baker
on the same page,

26:02.333 --> 26:03.567
busting ass.

26:03.600 --> 26:05.533
And then there's Chris.

26:05.567 --> 26:07.333
Don't be shy, Chris.

26:07.333 --> 26:08.433
- How do I--
- It's f---ing heavy.

26:08.467 --> 26:10.734
Just no respect at all.

26:10.734 --> 26:14.734
- Sorry.
The sky looks sick, man.

26:14.734 --> 26:16.467
- Hi.
You good?

