Can I have another
glass of rosé? Whoo!

38:11.767 --> 38:14.533
[laughter and cheering]

38:14.567 --> 38:16.333
- Oh, sh--!

38:16.367 --> 38:18.133
[Upbeat music slows, stops]

38:18.133 --> 38:19.667
- [yawns]

38:19.667 --> 38:21.266
- I am so sorry!
- It's okay.

38:21.300 --> 38:23.266
- Oh my God.

38:23.266 --> 38:25.633
- Another reason
to drink champagne, my friend.

38:25.667 --> 38:28.266
- You know who's really cute?
- Who?

38:28.300 --> 38:30.233
- Bri.
- I agree.

38:30.266 --> 38:32.667
- F---, I want to bang her.
- Do it.

38:32.700 --> 38:35.266
- It's gonna be
a work in progress.

38:35.266 --> 38:37.400
It's not gonna be--
- Got to put your time in.

38:37.433 --> 38:40.266
- Oh, you should go dance.
- No.

38:40.300 --> 38:44.367
- See, why are you saying no?
- 'Cause I'm tired.

38:44.400 --> 38:47.266
- It's okay if you don't have
a lot of deckhand experience,

38:47.300 --> 38:51.500
but it's not really the best
thing to tell the chief stew

38:51.533 --> 38:54.266
that you don't want to
'cause you're tired.

38:54.300 --> 38:56.500
- Sitting here doesn't mean that
I'm actually not doing anything.

38:56.533 --> 38:58.500
- It means
you're not doing much.

38:58.533 --> 39:00.533
You have to earn the tips,
just like all of us.

39:00.567 --> 39:02.433
- Oh, I haven't earned my tips?

39:02.433 --> 39:04.300
- I think--
- You think I don't work hard?

39:04.300 --> 39:05.633
You don't--you're not on
the deck to see how hard I work.

39:05.667 --> 39:07.567
- When there is an opportunity--

39:07.567 --> 39:09.400
- Yeah, but I need to be--
- For you to help out...

39:09.433 --> 39:11.266
- So why didn't told me
in the beginning of the dinner,

39:11.300 --> 39:12.700
or today that
"Bruno, you know what?

39:12.700 --> 39:14.166
"You're gonna do
something tonight,

39:14.166 --> 39:15.633
you're gonna dance upstairs."

39:15.667 --> 39:17.567
Not just because now
I'm sitting in the T, so, like--

39:17.600 --> 39:19.367
- Bruno, how much
advance notice do you need

39:19.400 --> 39:21.400
to participate in the charters?

39:21.433 --> 39:25.567
We need a cruise ship-style
conga line on the main deck aft.

39:25.567 --> 39:27.700
I thought this was, like,
the one thing he could do.

39:27.700 --> 39:29.300
We're all tired, but this
is why we get

39:29.333 --> 39:31.166
paid large amounts of money.

39:31.200 --> 39:34.333
- What's going on out there?
- Probably Kate.

39:34.367 --> 39:36.600
- You know, honestly,
the real reason that I'm upset

39:36.600 --> 39:39.333
is because of the response
that you're having right now.

39:39.333 --> 39:41.400
- Kate, you start
a conversation judging me.

39:41.433 --> 39:43.333
- I'm not judging you.
It's a fact.

39:43.367 --> 39:45.300
You have no yacht
deckhand experience.

39:45.333 --> 39:47.467
- You don't see me working
18 hours per day.

39:47.467 --> 39:49.667
Do you think I'm sleeping?
No, I'm working outside.

39:49.700 --> 39:52.266
So, if you don't understand
that, then you have an issue.

39:52.300 --> 39:54.567
[dramatic musical flourish]

39:55.767 --> 39:58.300
- [laughing]
- Girlfriend, it's bedtime.

39:58.333 --> 40:01.333
Turn it off, baby.
- Good night, girls!

40:01.333 --> 40:04.333
[smooth funky music]

40:04.333 --> 40:06.367
♪ ♪

40:08.467 --> 40:11.433
[idle marimba music]

40:11.467 --> 40:18.467
♪ ♪

40:27.400 --> 40:29.066
- I can take criticisms,
and I can be told

40:29.100 --> 40:31.567
when I've done something wrong.

40:31.600 --> 40:33.367
Instead, I get to figure out

40:33.367 --> 40:35.367
maybe I've done
something wrong,

40:35.400 --> 40:36.600
and then I just don't
get to sleep anymore,

40:36.633 --> 40:38.433
and I have to do anchor watch.

40:38.467 --> 40:40.700
Possibly more effective
would be to tell me,

40:40.734 --> 40:43.066
"These are the things
that are happening,

40:43.100 --> 40:45.467
and I hope we can see
some progress in the future."

40:45.500 --> 40:48.633
Instead, it's just like
the strangest middle finger

40:48.633 --> 40:50.600
I've gotten in a long time.

40:50.633 --> 40:52.700
♪ ♪

40:52.734 --> 40:55.700
[upbeat music]

40:55.734 --> 41:00.667
♪ ♪

41:00.667 --> 41:03.000
- Chris, Chris.
Go ahead and go down.

41:03.033 --> 41:06.133
♪ ♪

41:11.400 --> 41:14.000
[electronic music]

41:14.000 --> 41:15.667
- Oh!
- Yeah.

41:15.700 --> 41:17.667
- Look who's moving.

41:17.667 --> 41:21.367
- [groaning]
- Oh, there's an angry--

41:21.400 --> 41:24.100
- [laughs] No, it's not anger.

41:24.133 --> 41:25.400
It's just like, [groans]...

41:26.533 --> 41:27.767
- [laughs] Yeah.

41:28.000 --> 41:31.100
♪ ♪

41:31.133 --> 41:34.000
- You're engaged, and you
want to stay engaged.

41:34.033 --> 41:36.066
Anchor's ready on
your command, Captain.

41:36.100 --> 41:38.367
- Roger that. All right,
let's get this hook up.

41:38.400 --> 41:40.533
- You have to start
flaking that.

41:40.567 --> 41:42.166
It's at the waterline clean.

41:42.166 --> 41:44.433
I'm gonna bring it home.
Chop anchor.

41:44.433 --> 41:47.567
- Copy that.
We're out of here.

41:47.567 --> 41:50.700
[light music]

41:50.700 --> 41:54.033
- All right, so you can start
with these guys.

41:54.033 --> 41:56.433
- Looks so good. Thank you.

41:56.433 --> 41:59.400
- Our last meal.
- Oh my gosh.

41:59.433 --> 42:00.567
Those are the best
breakfast potatoes

42:00.567 --> 42:03.000
I've ever had in my life.

42:03.033 --> 42:04.500
- So, what's going on, anything?

42:04.533 --> 42:07.567
- So last night,
when we came down,

42:07.567 --> 42:10.633
Kate came, like,
with this weird conversation

42:10.667 --> 42:13.500
that I'm not basically
doing anything on board.

42:13.533 --> 42:16.567
Like, I don't have any yachting
experience--like, from nowhere,

42:16.600 --> 42:18.767
that I should be upstairs
dancing with the guests.

42:19.000 --> 42:20.567
Who she is, like, to tell me

42:20.567 --> 42:23.600
that I don't
do anything on board?

42:23.633 --> 42:26.567
- She does have a rank,
you know,

42:26.600 --> 42:28.734
which is understandable,
but at the same time

42:28.734 --> 42:31.066
she does need to learn,
you know, how to properly--

42:31.066 --> 42:32.600
- How to put the things on.
- Yeah.

42:32.633 --> 42:34.600
The last thing
on my mind is Kate.

42:34.633 --> 42:36.533
Right now
I'm just hoping we have

42:36.567 --> 42:38.567
a good docking here,
nice and easy.

42:38.600 --> 42:40.433
If she mentions it again,
just be like,

42:40.467 --> 42:42.600
"Listen, I'm doing
my job, all right?

42:42.600 --> 42:44.000
"If you have a problem
with what's going on,

42:44.033 --> 42:45.700
then go and talk to Nico."

42:45.734 --> 42:47.467
And I'll have no problem
explaining to her

42:47.500 --> 42:49.467
that we don't get breaks.

42:49.500 --> 42:51.667
- Yeah, exactly.
- So leave him alone.

42:54.066 --> 42:56.066
- Coming up...
- We got away with so much.

42:56.066 --> 42:58.200
And I can promise you,
there's gonna be a change

42:58.200 --> 43:00.066
in the configuration
of this crew.

43:00.066 --> 43:01.100
Count on it.

43:04.300 --> 43:04.700
[upbeat electronic music]

43:07.200 --> 43:09.767
♪ ♪

43:09.767 --> 43:11.500
- Can I get you
something to drink?

43:11.500 --> 43:12.767
- I would love a--
are we drinking yet?

43:13.000 --> 43:15.066
[laughter]
- Of course!

43:15.100 --> 43:16.633
- Bri was so funny yesterday.

43:16.633 --> 43:18.200
- She's hilarious.
- Yeah.

43:18.233 --> 43:19.734
- I love her.
- Me too.

43:19.767 --> 43:21.467
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

43:21.500 --> 43:22.734
- Is she your type?
- Yeah.

43:22.767 --> 43:24.166
- Really?
- Yeah.

43:24.200 --> 43:26.100
- Well, if we have a day off,

43:26.133 --> 43:27.767
you should go do something
adventurous with her.

43:27.767 --> 43:29.767
- Yeah. [laughs]

43:29.767 --> 43:31.633
- You guys could sail off
into the sunset together.

43:31.667 --> 43:33.500
- Wow. Oh my God.
- This could be your love boat.

43:33.533 --> 43:36.367
- I'm attacking the closet now.

43:36.400 --> 43:38.033
It's not even that full.

43:38.066 --> 43:40.500
- Oh my gosh,
I had such a good time.

43:40.500 --> 43:42.166
- And I want to say
I did something interesting

43:42.200 --> 43:44.233
last night during watch,
but I didn't.

43:44.266 --> 43:46.000
- Just as long as
we didn't drag anchor

43:46.000 --> 43:47.734
and you stayed awake.

43:47.767 --> 43:49.667
- Good all night.

43:49.667 --> 43:51.000
- All right, so let's get
ready on our line.

43:51.000 --> 43:52.533
- You didn't see anything?

43:52.533 --> 43:54.667
- I can't see that far.
No cleat?

43:54.667 --> 43:56.734
- No, the broken one is gone.

43:56.767 --> 43:59.100
- Chris, Chris?
- Go ahead.

43:59.133 --> 44:01.133
- Just a heads up,
that cleat is gone,

44:01.166 --> 44:03.633
so if that line doesn't
reach far enough,

44:03.667 --> 44:06.633
we're gonna use that other
aft-leading spring line.

44:06.667 --> 44:08.600
All right, so let's
get ready on our lines.

44:08.633 --> 44:11.000
The stern up first,
aft leading the spring.

44:11.033 --> 44:12.500
I'll tell you when to throw.

44:12.533 --> 44:13.767
- Okay.
- All right.

44:14.000 --> 44:15.600
Hopefully it's better
than last time.

44:15.633 --> 44:17.533
- After we hit to dock,
this deck crew

44:17.533 --> 44:19.533
scares the hell out of me,
and I'm fearless.

44:19.533 --> 44:22.667
And with this docking,
hopefully they'll perform.

44:22.667 --> 44:25.233
If not, heads will roll.

44:25.266 --> 44:27.700
Oh my God. All right,
I got no bow thruster.

44:27.734 --> 44:29.700
- (BLEEP)
- Oh, f--.

44:29.734 --> 44:32.033
- Bow line down.
- Oh, God.

44:32.033 --> 44:34.233
- Lock the bow line down.
Hold as much slack as you can.

44:34.266 --> 44:38.033
- When your captain says,
"I am bow thruster-less,"

44:38.033 --> 44:40.033
and your crew doesn't know
what they're doing...

44:40.066 --> 44:41.233
- Does it help if you swing it?

44:41.266 --> 44:43.166
- It's--it's bad.

44:43.166 --> 44:45.033
It's really--
get really bad, really quick.

44:45.033 --> 44:46.100
- If you're gonna
throw that thing, get it

44:46.133 --> 44:48.033
to the goddamn dock.

44:48.033 --> 44:49.266
- We've got to have those
heaving lines ready.

44:49.300 --> 44:50.633
Pull, pull, pull, pull, pull.

44:50.667 --> 44:52.000
Fast, fast, fast.

44:52.033 --> 44:53.266
- Valor is an older boat.

44:53.300 --> 44:55.133
Hold up on that spring line.

44:55.166 --> 44:57.033
I'm gonna try and
get the stern in now.

44:57.033 --> 44:59.000
That thruster's got
limited capabilities.

44:59.033 --> 45:01.567
I can hold us there for a while,
but it's not infinite.

45:01.567 --> 45:03.100
- Pull up on that line.
Right there. That's slacking.

45:03.133 --> 45:05.100
Matt comes out of nowhere.

45:05.133 --> 45:07.166
I didn't ask him to come out.
He just did it.

45:07.200 --> 45:09.066
How does my yacht chef
know what to do

45:09.066 --> 45:11.533
in this situation
better than my deckhands?

45:11.567 --> 45:13.166
- Is the bow line locked down?
If you can't talk, shake--

45:13.200 --> 45:15.266
- Yes, sir. Bow line's
locked down. Get that ready.

45:15.300 --> 45:17.700
- I need slack on the stern line
in order to kick the bow in.

45:17.734 --> 45:19.600
- Take it off.
You can't pull it up if it's

45:19.633 --> 45:21.066
wrapped around the bollard.
Pull, pull, pull.

45:21.066 --> 45:22.734
- Are we taken up
on the stern line?

45:22.734 --> 45:24.600
- That's good on the stern
there, Cap.

45:24.600 --> 45:26.133
Go ahead and lock
those lines off, guys.

45:26.166 --> 45:28.734
- Thanks, Matt.
- No worries.

45:28.767 --> 45:31.300
- If I get on the radio and I
say with an experienced crew,

45:31.333 --> 45:35.033
"I've lost the thruster," they
instinctively know what to do.

45:35.066 --> 45:38.033
With this crew, it just
compounds the problem.

45:38.066 --> 45:39.567
- Grab that. Now, tie it up.

45:39.600 --> 45:41.533
- All right,
he's got it on, pull it tight.

45:41.567 --> 45:43.600
- Did you see them wrapping
that thing like that?

45:43.600 --> 45:45.533
- Well, that sure as (BLEEP)
was a dog and pony show.

45:45.567 --> 45:48.200
- Yeah. F---ing
embarrassing, again.

45:48.200 --> 45:50.633
- I need everyone
on the main deck aft.

45:50.633 --> 45:53.767
[upbeat music]

45:53.767 --> 45:55.633
- Have safe travels.
It was very good to meet you.

45:55.633 --> 45:57.066
- Thank you. Nice meeting you.
Thank you, guys.

45:57.100 --> 45:58.633
all: Thank you.

45:58.667 --> 46:00.633
- Wonderful to meet you.
- Thank you.

46:00.633 --> 46:02.367
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

46:02.367 --> 46:05.233
- [soft laugh]

46:05.233 --> 46:09.100
- Thank you guys so much.
We had such a great time.

46:09.133 --> 46:11.066
This is for--
this is for you guys.

46:11.100 --> 46:12.767
We appreciate you guys
more than anything.

46:13.000 --> 46:14.033
And [kisses]
love you guys all!

46:14.066 --> 46:16.734
all: Bye!

46:19.233 --> 46:21.734
- I need everybody in
the crew mess in five minutes.

46:21.767 --> 46:24.633
[hip-hop instrumental music]

46:24.667 --> 46:31.367
♪ ♪

46:35.367 --> 46:37.133
I thought we had
a good charter.

46:37.133 --> 46:40.533
Your food was killer.
- Thank you.

46:40.567 --> 46:42.667
- Your girls did
a good job on service.

46:42.667 --> 46:46.333
I was pleased with that.
Making progress.

46:46.367 --> 46:48.233
Um.

46:50.266 --> 46:53.600
I was party to two of the worst
dockings and undockings

46:53.633 --> 46:55.367
I've ever been involved with.

46:55.400 --> 46:58.100
They were just
f---ing atrocious.

46:58.133 --> 47:04.000
And we got so lucky and
got away with so much, somehow.

47:04.000 --> 47:07.000
I don't know what to do.

47:07.000 --> 47:10.667
But I do know that it can't
continue the way it's going.

47:10.667 --> 47:12.166
And I can promise you

47:12.200 --> 47:14.033
there's gonna be a change in

47:14.033 --> 47:15.567
the configuration
of this crew.

47:15.600 --> 47:18.567
Count on it.

47:18.567 --> 47:22.567
- I hope that Lee just cans
one of these f---ers.

47:22.567 --> 47:25.567
I'll sacrifice Chris.
Send him packing.

47:25.567 --> 47:28.300
I'll pay for his plane ticket
to go home.

47:28.333 --> 47:31.567
- On a better note,
the girls left us a nice tip.

47:31.600 --> 47:35.300
It's very respectable.
16 grand.

47:35.300 --> 47:37.700
I think we end up
with 1,540 each.

47:37.700 --> 47:39.567
Matt.
- Thank you.

47:39.567 --> 47:41.533
- Kate.

47:41.567 --> 47:43.400
Goodness.

47:43.433 --> 47:45.567
Nico.
- Thank you, sir.

47:45.600 --> 47:49.100
- So, we've got to get
the boat flipped.

47:49.133 --> 47:50.700
That's a wrap.
Let's get to it.

47:50.700 --> 47:52.533
- Thank you.

47:52.567 --> 47:54.266
[upbeat music]

47:54.300 --> 47:55.333
- Whoa.

47:55.333 --> 47:57.200
♪ ♪

47:57.200 --> 47:59.166
- So, what did you think
of the tip meeting?

47:59.200 --> 48:01.000
- Like, does that mean
somebody's going home?

48:01.033 --> 48:04.333
- I can't tell if Captain Lee
is saying that so that--

48:04.333 --> 48:06.200
- To scare them silly?
- Yeah.

48:06.200 --> 48:08.200
- I just wanted to talk
about the charter.

48:08.200 --> 48:11.066
Like, for instance, when we got
off the dock, you know,

48:11.066 --> 48:13.266
you guys were hanging out
on the aft deck kind of talking.

48:13.300 --> 48:16.066
Okay, dockhands are here?
Okay, we're ready, right?

48:16.100 --> 48:18.600
Well, no one noticed
the tender line was tied on top.

48:18.633 --> 48:20.700
When we take these lines off,

48:20.734 --> 48:23.700
this whole entire top bit
needs to already be undone.

48:23.734 --> 48:26.200
- For me, it is
scary hearing Captain

48:26.200 --> 48:28.033
saying that change
is gonna happen.

48:28.066 --> 48:30.033
I think I'm doing a good job,

48:30.066 --> 48:32.200
but I don't feel confident
I'm gonna stay at all.

48:32.200 --> 48:34.266
- Take the initiative.

48:34.300 --> 48:36.367
- I feel like Captain Lee
doesn't know who to send home.

48:36.400 --> 48:38.367
- Oh my gosh, that's so sad.

48:38.400 --> 48:42.200
- People on yachts are fired
for much less, usually.

48:42.233 --> 48:43.633
- Oh, I know.

48:43.633 --> 48:44.767
- You know, if Lee, he's gonna

48:44.767 --> 48:46.767
figure something out on Tuesday.

48:46.767 --> 48:48.700
Hopefully, you know,
he just says, "You know what?

48:48.734 --> 48:51.066
Scratch it, make sure
they know their sh--."

48:51.100 --> 48:53.233
If not, then somebody
might be going home.

48:53.266 --> 48:56.333
- If Captain wants to make
a change, he should do it.

48:56.367 --> 48:58.433
Or he can say,
"Change is coming,"

48:58.467 --> 49:00.767
and make everybody
more stressed out,

49:00.767 --> 49:02.767
and more worried for their job,

49:02.767 --> 49:05.233
and decrease
work performance even more.

49:05.233 --> 49:08.100
I don't think that's wise,
but that's Captain.

49:08.133 --> 49:10.200
- Let's just move on.
Let's put everything away.

49:10.233 --> 49:13.767
Do a deck check,
and be done working.

49:14.000 --> 49:16.066
- Didn't have to happen.
- No, no.

49:16.100 --> 49:18.000
- But it's not major.

49:19.266 --> 49:22.200
[upbeat music]

49:22.233 --> 49:24.000
- We're going
to dinner tonight.

49:24.000 --> 49:26.000
And we're going dancing.
- I love it.

49:26.000 --> 49:27.667
Should I wear a different bra
that's not showing?

49:27.667 --> 49:29.467
- No, I like that lace.

49:30.400 --> 49:32.133
- Thank you. I like yours too.

49:32.133 --> 49:34.000
- All right,
let's get out of here.

49:34.000 --> 49:35.667
- Yeah. Let's go.
Let's get out of here.

49:35.667 --> 49:37.400
- What's up, Baker?
- What's up, Nico?

49:37.400 --> 49:39.266
- How's everything going? Good?

49:39.266 --> 49:41.133
- Yeah.
- Good.

49:41.166 --> 49:44.100
- How about you?
- Yeah, life is good, you know?

49:48.166 --> 49:50.400
- Big changes are gonna be made
with the deck team.

49:50.400 --> 49:52.333
Nothing we can do about that.

49:52.367 --> 49:54.400
I think we're just gonna
go party our ass off,

49:54.400 --> 49:56.233
because this might be
our last night together.

49:56.266 --> 49:59.166
- Whoo, cheers.

49:59.200 --> 50:02.166
[electronic dance music]

50:02.200 --> 50:04.533
♪ ♪

50:04.567 --> 50:06.100
- Ooh!
- Oh!

50:06.133 --> 50:09.367
♪ ♪

50:26.433 --> 50:30.033
♪ ♪

50:30.033 --> 50:32.200
- Whoo!

50:34.066 --> 50:37.033
Kate is out to make
my life a living hell.

50:37.033 --> 50:41.066
So, I've learned
to embrace every moment I can.

50:41.066 --> 50:43.033
So just f---ing let go.

50:53.433 --> 50:55.000
- [laughs]

50:57.467 --> 50:58.433
- Please say yes.
Please say yes.

50:58.467 --> 50:59.500
Serious?

51:05.367 --> 51:06.433
[upbeat club music playing]

51:18.300 --> 51:19.266
All right.

51:19.300 --> 51:24.000
♪ ♪

51:35.500 --> 51:37.233
- Oh, God, that was fun.

51:37.233 --> 51:40.633
- I need the back!
